sequenceDiagram
    participant Caller as Trace Harness / Caller
    participant Inventory as IBridgeToolInventoryService
    participant Catalog as IBridgeToolCatalog
    participant Compiled as CompiledBridgeToolDiscovery
    participant MEF as MefBridgeToolDiscovery
    participant Descriptor as BridgeToolDescriptor
    participant Manifest as BridgeToolManifest
    participant Snapshot as BridgeToolCatalogSnapshot

    Caller->>Inventory: GetSnapshot()
    Inventory->>Catalog: GetTools()
    Catalog->>Compiled: DiscoverTools()
    Compiled-->>Catalog: RegexTextSearchTool + Bm25TextSearchTool descriptors
    Catalog-->>Inventory: descriptors
    loop each descriptor
        Inventory->>Descriptor: read Manifest
        Descriptor->>Manifest: derive identity/version/category/discovery/host/risk/execution
        Manifest-->>Inventory: read-only metadata
    end
    Inventory->>Snapshot: create items sorted by tool id
    Snapshot-->>Caller: bridge.bm25TextSearch, bridge.regexTextSearch

    Caller->>Inventory: GetSnapshot() with MEF directory discovery enabled
    Inventory->>Catalog: GetTools()
    Catalog->>Compiled: DiscoverTools()
    Compiled-->>Catalog: compiled descriptors
    Catalog->>MEF: DiscoverTools()
    MEF-->>Catalog: fake.mef descriptor from shared-test export
    Catalog-->>Inventory: compiled + MEF descriptors
    loop each descriptor
        Inventory->>Descriptor: read Manifest
        Descriptor->>Manifest: derive manifest metadata
        Manifest-->>Inventory: read-only inventory metadata
    end
    Inventory->>Snapshot: create items sorted by tool id
    Snapshot-->>Caller: bridge.bm25TextSearch, bridge.regexTextSearch, fake.mef

    Note over Inventory,Catalog: Inventory reads descriptor/manifests only; it does not call tool ExecuteAsync.
    Note over Caller,Snapshot: No MCP transport behavior or tool execution boundary changes are part of this trace.
